@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Build Program";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Sports Website</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #000435;
            color: #D4AF37;
            height: 140vh;
        }

        header {
            background: #D4AF37;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .logo {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
        }

        nav ul {
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
        }

            nav ul li {
                margin-left: 1rem;
            }

                nav ul li a {
                    color: #fff;
                    text-decoration: none;
                }

        .cta {
            background: #D4AF37;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .hero {
            background: url('images/hero.jpg') no-repeat center center/cover;
            height: 60vh;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .hero-text h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
        }

        .hero-text p {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        section {
            padding: 2rem 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h2 {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .events, .news, .team-grid, .testimonial-carousel, .sponsor-logos {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 1rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .event-card, .news-card, .team-card, .testimonial-card {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            width: 30%;
        }

            .event-card img, .news-card img, .team-card img, .testimonial-card img {
                max-width: 100%;
                border-radius: 5px;
            }

        .sponsor-logos img {
            max-width: 10%;
            margin: 0 1rem;
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
        }

        .newsletter form {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .newsletter input {
            padding: 0.5rem;
            font-size: 1rem;
            border: 1px solid #fff;
            border-radius: 5px 0 0 5px;
        }

        .newsletter button {
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            font-size: 1rem;
            border: none;
            background: #D4AF37;
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
        }

        footer {
            background: #D4AF37;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

            footer .quick-links, footer .social-media, footer .contact-info {
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
            }

            footer a {
                color: #fff;
                text-decoration: none;
                margin: 0 0.5rem;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-6">Build Program</h1>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-9">Rehab Phase 1: Pain Relief and Range of Motion</h1>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <p>This is right after an injury happens. You may be experiencing pain, swelling, and limited use of the injured area. Swelling during this phase is also very easy to trigger with light use, so even if it feels okay at rest it starts to hurt as soon as you use it. Phase 1 can last anywhere from 1-3 weeks and our focus will be on reducing your pain and swelling and getting you moving again.</p>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-9">Goals for phase 1:</h1>
</div>

<li>No pain at rest</li>
<li>Reduction in swelling- Swelling should be down and not flared up with light, day to day tasks</li>
<li>80% range of motion</li>

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-9">Rehab Phase 2: Targeted Strengthening and Improving Function</h1>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <p>This is when your injury has started to heal and can handle some strengthening exercises. Exercise in this phase is what people typically think of when they think “rehab” and are targeted exercises meant to address specific weakness. Your exercises may start out fairly basic, targeting specific muscles, and progress in to larger, more functional movements</p>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-9">Goals for phase 2:</h1>
</div>

<li>Able to complete day to day activities without pain</li>
<li>Full, pain free range of motion</li>
<li>Equal strength from side to side</li>
<li>Improved confidence in using the affected area</li>

    <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="display-9">Rehab Phase 3: Functional Training </h1>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
        <p>Phase 3 is when you get to start using all of that hard-earned strength. Our focus here is to get you back to life, work, or sports. This includes exercises involving pushing, pulling, lifting, pressing, and squatting. This phase is closer to a ‘normal’ strength training workout, and by the end of this our goal is full recovery!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="display-9">Goals for phase 3:</h1>
    </div>

    <li>Full recovery!</li>
</body>
</html>